article.description: — Spencer Rodgers had 22 points as Kennesaw State defeated Eastern Kentucky 82-73 on Tuesday night in the first round of the Atlantic Sun Conference tournament.
article.headline: Kennesaw State tops Eastern Kentucky in Atlantic Sun tourney
article.linkText: Kennesaw State tops Eastern Kentucky in Atlantic Sun tourney
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. -- — Spencer Rodgers had 22 points as Kennesaw State defeated Eastern Kentucky 82-73 on Tuesday night in the first round of the Atlantic Sun Conference tournament. Demond Robinson had 18 points for Kennesaw State (13-17). Terrell Burden added 15 points and eight assists. Rodgers hit 6 of 9 3-pointers. Devontae Blanton had 23 points and eight rebounds for the Colonels (13-18). Jomaru Brown added 22 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
